OL,6,FMichelle Colborne, KC, mitigating for
OL,7,FLisa Ellwood, said the defendant had
OL,8,Fsaid she had no memory of the events
OL,9,Fleading up to the killing and that a
OL,10,Fpsychiatrist noted that this was
OL,11,Flikely to be due to alcohol.
OL,13,FMs Colborne said Lisa Ellwood had been
OL,14,Fsuffering a number of disorders
OL,15,Fincluding complex PTDS and a
OL,16,Fpersonality disorder.
OL,18,FAn expert had suggested that the
OL,19,Foffence would not have happened in the
OL,20,Fabsence of alcohol.
